<h2>Getting help</h2>

<h3>Mailing lists</h3>

<p>There are two <b>igraph</b> mailing lists: <code>igraph-help</code>
and <code>igraph-announce</code>.</p>

<p><code>igraph-help</code> is for general discussion and questions,
help, suggestions, etc. See
<a href="http://lists.nongnu.org/mailman/listinfo/igraph-help"
<!-- onClick="javascript:urchinTracker ('/outgoing/mailinglist-help'); " -->
>its page at Savannah</a> for subscription and archives.</p>

<p><code>igraph-announce</code> is a very low-traffic mailing (about one email per month) list for
important announcements only, such as a new <b>igraph</b> release for
example. <code>igraph-announce</code> is a read-only list, you can not
post any messages to it. See
<a href="http://lists.nongnu.org/mailman/listinfo/igraph-announce"
<!-- onClick="javascript:urchinTracker ('/outgoing/mailinglist-announce'); " -->
>its page at Savannah</a> for subscription and archives.</p>

<h3>Bug reports, questions, comments</h3>

<p>Please send questions, comments and bug reports to the
<a href="mailto:igraph-help@nongnu.org"><code>igraph-help</code>
mailing list</a> or to <a href="mailto:csardi@rmki.kfki.hu">Gábor
Csárdi</a>. The mailing list is preferred. In order to receive
responses to your comments, please consider subscribing to the
mailing list.</p>
